&lt;h2 id=&#34;prisoners-dilemma&#34;&gt;Prisoner&amp;rsquo;s Dilemma&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two criminals, i=1,2 are arrested for a serous crime and detained in separate cells. During separate interrogation,
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If both &amp;ldquo;confess&amp;rdquo;, they will be jailed for 5 years.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If bot &amp;ldquo;don&amp;rsquo;t confess&amp;rdquo;, they will be jailed for 1 year.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If player 1 confesses while player 2 does not, then player 1 will be freed and player 2 will be jailed for 10 years.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vice versa&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Formally define the game as
$$\Gamma={I,{S_i}&lt;em&gt;{i\in N}, {\nu_i(\cdot)}&lt;/em&gt;{i\in N}}$$
$$I={1, 2}$$
$$S_1=S_2={c,d}$$
$$u_1(c,c)=u_2(c,c)=-5$$
$$u_1(c,d)=u_2(d,c)=0$$
$$u_1(d,c)=u_2(c,d)=-10$$
$$u_1(d,d)=u_2(d,d)=-1$$&lt;/p&gt;
